headline: Union organizers inside Wells Fargo eye first victory at a nonbranch unit
summary: The unionization push by members of the bank's conduct management intake team has been hotly contested. If approved, it would represent a landmark in the effort to organize workers at the $1.9 trillion-asset bank.

headline: Stocks Will Scale This 'Wall of Worry,' Harvey Says
summary: -- Chris Harvey, Wells Fargo head of equity strategy, says stocks and risk will both go higher next year as the Federal Reserve slowly cuts rates. He is on Bloomberg Surveillance....
